  22:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s_ex.c ****                     ##### I2S Extension features #####
  23:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s_ex.c ****   ==============================================================================
  24:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s_ex.c ****   [..]
  25:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s_ex.c ****      (#) In I2S full duplex mode, each SPI peripheral is able to manage sending and receiving
  26:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s_ex.c ****          data simultaneously using two data lines. Each SPI peripheral has an extended block
  27:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s_ex.c ****          called I2Sxext (i.e I2S2ext for SPI2 and I2S3ext for SPI3).
  28:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s_ex.c ****      (#) The extension block is not a full SPI IP, it is used only as I2S slave to
  29:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s_ex.c ****          implement full duplex mode. The extension block uses the same clock sources
  30:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2s_ex.c ****          as its master.
ARM GAS  /var/folders/kf/d797ysj14bb1pb7szkr3jbx80000gn/T//ccybKxu7.s 			page 2


